The paper discusses the construction of characteristic matrixes for approximating concepts, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the handling of large amounts of data and the updating of matrices over time, which are relevant to data management (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical algorithms and techniques, which are often studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
